Dynamic networks updating for Pb, Pn, Pr networks

Source: R/make_bnr.R
make_bnr.Rd

`make_bnr()` returns an adjacency matrix.

make_bnr(n, pb, pn, pr, singleparent)

Arguments

n

Number of vertices (population size)
pb

Probability to connect to parent (default is 1)
pn

Probability to connect to neighbour of parent(s)
pr

Probability to connect to individuals that are not connected to the parent
singleparent

Logical. If TRUE the focal individual connects to one parent with probability pb. If FALSE the individual connects to two parents each with probability pb. Default is TRUE.

Value

Function returns an adjacncy-matrix.
